We tried this spot on a whim.  It was cold, it was late, we were hungry and we just stumbled upon it.   We were seated and served quickly.  Staff was relatively friendly.  The food is your typical American grub served in a classical/gastro pub ambiance.  Nothing that we had stood out as being out of the ordinary but nothing was bad.  Everything seemed relatively average.  We enjoyed our meals and if ever in the area again, we would pay another visit.

The Server we had (Michelle) provided the worst service. We had to constantly call her back to our table to get basic things like condiments, napkins and water, she served 1 or 2 people and brought their food before us when we arrived earlier and they provide specials on Tuesdays, which we asked about when sat and she charged us regular price. When brought to her attention, she tried to insist that she was giving us a deal when she wasn't. On Tuesdays, the Louie Nation app affords you to get Craft burgers and 2 beer/wine for a price. We asked about that and she said as long as you have the app it is that. She never checked back or asked if we did after the conversation, she just charged us full price and attempted to play it off like she did us a favor. She eventually changed the bill once she verified that BOTH of us had enrolled in the app eventhough I was the one paying. I definitely prefer the Bar Louie near the HOB or in Hyde Park to this one. There was a Black waitress that wasn't even our server that provided us better service than our own. I initially gave 2 stars, but I'm going down to one. Poor, poor, poor service.

This review is strictly for their happy hour. I came to Bar Louie with a friend recently and was excited to learn that they had their HH going when we got there. Bar Louie has a great HH! Probably one of the best I've seen in Chicago. They have half off appetizers and $5 martinis and discounts on beer (but I don't remember specifically) from 4-7PM Monday through Friday! We opted for the boneless chicken wings ($6.50 during HH) and pepperoni flatbread ($6 during HH). The wings came with ranch and blue cheese dressing. The wings were decent, I would say a bit on the salty side. I enjoyed the pepperoni flatbread. Both of these were good portion sizes. My friend and I both got the "Effen good" martini which was delicious!! It was so refreshing with flavors of cucumber and just a bit of sweetness. Also loved their outdoor seating on a nice summer day! Would definitely come back here for HH but not sure if I'd pay full price for their apps.

Between DJing in bars for 5 years, and spending 7 in the industry as a bouncer I have yet to see an employee who cares about their customers the way Nixxi does. She at one point even traded a table with another server so she could help us. I genuinely hope her managers see this and appreciate her for the dedicated employee she is. Overall: While certainly not the worst option in the area, only come for the drinks and not for food.  The good: The wings, compared to the rest of the food, were tasty. The teriyaki and buffalo sauces were savory and not overpowering. The event space that we had in the back was accommodating and separated well enough from the rest of the bar.  The not-so-good: The rest of our food was pretty disappointing, and that was the universal consensus with the rest of the group. The quesadilla was flat and consisted of nothing but cheese, the chips and guac were stale, and the egg rolls cold and flavorless. Other than those and the wings, I didn't dare try anything else.  Atmosphere: 7/10 Service: 6/10 Food: 4/10
